[3] Middle East (Syria)
Date: Sun 17 Dec 2022
Source: Enab Baladi [In Arabic, trans., edited]
https://www.enabbaladi.net/archives/619284


The "Self [autonomous] Administration" in northeastern Syria announced the suspension of school activities in Al-Raqqa governorate, days after the death of children from a suspected "influenza" disease [infection].

According to the decision circulated by the "Administration" to its educational departments today, Sat 17 Dec 2022, a copy of which was seen by Enab Baladi, the holiday extends from 18 to 24 Dec 2022.

The decision issued by the co-presidency of the "Raqqa Civil Council" stated that the decision to suspend working hours came at the recommendation of the "Health Committee" of the "Autonomous Administration" due to the bad weather and the spread of the "influenza."

--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Mahmoud Orabi

[ProMED map of Syria: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8707295,28175

Overall the reports above indicate increased influenza activity, with an early surge reported from many countries.

The report from Syria ([3] above) may potentially indicate other respiratory pathogens in addition to influenza, including bacterial causes. However, limited diagnostic capacity for diagnosis of non-influenza viruses and bacteria may lead to misdiagnosis and/or delay in treatment. - Mod.UBA]
